<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/53201AKJTJLSKDPDLPTMDVPTDGSNGNBPL> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Vancouver International Mountain Film Festival";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">Hosted by Matt Dennison & Dylan Tremblay</span><span><br/></span>Join us for an inspiring event as the VIMFF World Tour brings the spirit of mountain exploration to your city. This special screening features a curated selection of award-winning films from the Vancouver International Mountain Film Festival — stories that celebrate mountain culture, human endurance, and the beauty of our planet.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>VIMFF is more than just a film festival — it's a global outdoor community. The films chosen for this tour span a wide spectrum: from high-stakes climbing and snowsports to mountain biking, environmental journeys, and culturally rich storytelling. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Many of them are deeply immersive, pushing the limits of human potential and exploring how people relate to mountains, nature, and each other. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Meet Your Hosts</span><span><br/></span>We are stoked to welcome two icons of the Canadian riding and filmmaking scene to the stage:<span><br/></span>•	<span class=\"BoldText\">Matt Dennison</span>: A creative powerhouse who turned filming his friends into a massive career. With over a million subscribers and 400+ million views, Matt is the master of blending the outdoors with comedy and cinematic visuals for brands like Red Bull and Trek.<span><br/></span>•	<span class=\"BoldText\">Dylan Tremblay</span>: A legendary freerider and star of the influential Drop In TV series. Back from a hiatus and riding stronger than ever, Dylan brings a wealth of mountain culture knowledge and a deep passion for the sport (ask him about his collection of 150+ vintage bikes!).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Door Prizes & Community Vibes</span><span><br/></span>To celebrate our local community, we’re giving away door prizes generously donated by local businesses and bike shops. Arrive early — you won’t want to miss your chance to win some great gear and catch up with fellow outdoor enthusiasts!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Come be part of the festival that not only entertains, but uplifts and inspires. Whether you're passionate about outdoor adventure, environmental issues, or just love a good story — this is an event for you.<span><br/></span>
""";
